    {
      "instruction": "<p>Add your <strong>trimmed green beans</strong> to a pot, cover them with <strong>boiled water</strong> (just enough to cover them) with a pinch of<strong> salt</strong></p><p>Bring to the boil over a high heat and cook for 5-6 min or until tender</p><p>Return the potatoes to a low heat with the <strong>remaining</strong> <strong>butter</strong> and a splash of <strong>milk</strong></p><p>Season with a generous pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and mash until smooth – this is your<strong> sweet potato mash</strong></p>",
